# Project stack — earth-explorers-3d

**3D Visuals** — interactive 3D Earth observation experiences (React Three Fiber, satellite mission content). **GitLab** monorepo. Agents usually touch **`visuals-portal/`**; related images and Helm charts live beside it at the repo root.

| Area | This repository |
| ---- | ---------------- |
| **FE app** | **`visuals-portal/`** — Next.js **13** (Pages Router, `src/pages/`), React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, React Three Fiber / **drei**, Zustand, SWR, **iron-session** + **openid-client** (OIDC), Matomo (**`@socialgouv/matomo-next`**), **`next-pwa`** |
| **Reverse proxy image** | **`visuals-nginx/`** — paired with portal deploys (see root **`/.gitlab-ci.yml`** triggers) |
| **Data scripts** | **`aeolus-data-script/`**, **`earthcare-data-script/`** — small Node tooling (only when editing those folders) |
| **Repo tooling** | **`scripts/`** — **`npm run sync:collections`** and related helpers for **`third-party/cursor-collections`** |
| **Deploy** | **Helm** under **`charts/`** — **`visuals-portal`**, **`visuals-nginx`**; environment values under **`charts/environments/`** (e.g. **`dev/`**, **`prod/`**) |
| **CI** | **GitLab** — root **`/.gitlab-ci.yml`** forwards to **`visuals-portal/.gitlab-ci.yml`** and **`visuals-nginx/.gitlab-ci.yml`** when those paths change |
| **Cursor framework** | Submodule **`third-party/cursor-collections`** — [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md), rules **`/.cursor/rules/`**, prompts **`@eversis-*`**, **`eversis-collections`** MCP |

There is **no** single root **`package.json`** application workspace — run commands from **`visuals-portal/`** for the portal, or **`scripts/`** / **`third-party/`** as documented below.

## Quality commands — run from `visuals-portal/`

Use **yarn** in **`visuals-portal/`**:

| Check | Command |
| --- | --- |
| **Lint** | `yarn lint` |
| **Lint + format fixes** | `yarn lint:fix` |
| **Format check** | `yarn format:check` |
| **Production build** | `yarn build` |
| **Dev server** | `yarn dev` |

GitLab (**`visuals-portal/.gitlab-ci.yml`**) runs **`yarn install --frozen-lockfile`**, **`yarn lint`**, and **`yarn build`**. There is **no `yarn test` script** in this package today; rely on **lint** and **build** before hand-off unless a ticket adds automated tests.

**Node:** Root **`README.md`** recommends Node **v21+** for local work; **`visuals-portal`** CI images use **Node 22** (`node:22-alpine`).

### Bun helpers (`visuals-portal/` only)

GeoJSON maintenance scripts (**`yarn transform-geojson`**, **`stream-geojson`**, **`mergeGeoJSON`**) invoke **Bun** per **`visuals-portal/package.json`** — use only when working those pipelines.

### Cursor collections sync (`scripts/`)

First-time / after submodule bumps — see root **`README.md`**. Typical:

```bash
cd scripts
npm run sync:collections
```

Optional flags are documented on **`scripts/sync-cursor-collections.mjs`** (e.g. **`--check-only`**, MCP build/start).

## Conventions

- **Specs / plans:** **`docs/specs/<issue-kebab>/`** — `*.research.md`, `*.plan.md` (see **`docs/specs/README.md`**).
- **Internal notes:** **`docs/context/*.md`** (see **`docs/context/README.md`** when present).
- **Git commits:** JIRA-style first line — see **`AGENTS.md`** and team practice (use branch / ticket id when supplied).
- **Package manager:** **Yarn 1.x** in **`visuals-portal/`**; do **not** add conflicting lockfiles or new package-manager dependencies without lead agreement (**`eversis-agent-core.mdc`**).

## Integration branches

**`visuals-portal/.gitlab-ci.yml`** runs on **`develop`**, **`azure-develop`**, branch patterns **`/^uat.*/`** and **`/^XJ3D.*/`**, and **`/^release-.*/`** (see **`only:`** in that file). Root **`.gitlab-ci.yml`** also keys **`master`**, **`azure-develop`**, and **`release-*`** for image pipelines. Align MR targets with team workflow.

## Status: Fine — QA comment (mandatory contract)

When **all** planned agent work for the Implement thread is finished:

1. Declare **`Fine`** (explicit word / status).
2. **In the same assistant response** as **`Fine`**, produce the **QA comment draft** per **`.cursor/skills/eversis-qa-comment/SKILL.md`** in Cursor Collections (read via MCP **`eversis_skills_get`** for **`eversis-qa-comment`** when MCP is enabled).
3. Label the draft: **`Draft QA comment — review before posting to Jira`**.
4. **Never** post to Jira in that turn; publication only after **explicit** human approval.

Skipping the QA draft when declaring **Fine** is a **workflow breach** — if you cannot comply (context limit, blocked tools), say so and stop **without** declaring **Fine**.
